features: Lil' Peepers are gentle individually wrapped baby eye wipes come 30 eye wipes per box with shelf life of 4 years. Use as general baby eye cleaning and lid scrubs for eyes.
Provides gentle moisturizing and soothing relief to baby's delicate eye area. For extra relief, eye lid wipes can be cooled before use. Helps alleviate clogged tear ducts.
Each soothing wipe is individually wrapped in its own sachet for extra moisture and safety for irritated eyes. Provides soothing relief from irritants such as dust, pet dander. Made in Israel.
Paraben-free, preservative free, alcohol-free, fragrance-free and rinse free. Ophthalmologically tested and hypoallergenic. Recommended by pediatricians.
Safe for use and very effective for all age groups to clean conjunctivitis and clogged tear ducts along with pink eye, dry eye, styes & allergies, eases eye irritations.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: When your baby's gorgeous little eyes are exploring the world around them in wonder, it's heart-breaking to see them become sore and gunky. It can happen regularly too, as those adventurous little peepers can be affected by all sorts of irritants and allergies. It's so important to keep them clean and soothed with a kind tear-free formula that you trust. Lil’ Peepers Eyelid Cleansing Wipes are designed to clean and soothe kids’ eyes from gunk and mess caused by allergies, irritation, or crying, and help to prevent infection and vision problems. Our Eyelid Wipes are individually wrapped for convenient, on-the-go care. No water or rinsing necessary.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Was a bit skeptical because I needed to use them in my newborn that had a clogged tear duct but they worked wonderfully. They didn’t irritate the babies delicate skin and it took off the gunk super quick

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Es un esencial sin duda
reviews.reviewText: Mi bebé de mes y medio inicio con secreciones en un ojito, constantemente tenía que limpiar el área ocular y con miedo a que el alcohol u otros químicos de las toallas húmedas pudieran tener me di a la tarea de buscar y encontré estas y desde entonces no las he cambiado. Son una maravilla, quisiera que hubiese una caja con más unidades porque me he olvidado de recomprar a tiempo. Son fantásticas y muy suaves .

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for Infants Clogged Tear Duct
reviews.reviewText: Our infant son had a clogged tear duct for 7 months and would often wake with crust on his eye. We used these wipes to help clear that crust and keep his eye clear. They were very gentle and did not bother or irritate him at all. I liked the single use packages because I knew they were clean and sterile with each use. I could also throw in the diaper bag and bring along on the go. They worked great for us!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pricey but works well!
reviews.reviewText: Worked very well and was tear free! Didn’t bother my son when I was using them on him. I highly recommend for children with blocked tear ducks. The only con is that it is expensive for the amount of wiped you receive although they do work well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These are great handy eye wipes with plenty of saline solution on each swab. Used daily to clear a blocked tear duct, on the mend now!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I can’t believe they worked!
reviews.reviewText: My son has had an issue with his tear duct draining since he was born. His pediatrician kept saying it should clear up, but at 10 months old, I was beginning to fear he might need a surgical procedure because absolutely nothing was helping. I was skeptical about this product but I was desperate. I wiped his affected eye multiple times a day, and lo and behold, by day 5 his eye had cleared up!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 1, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great wipes for infant blocked tear duct!
reviews.reviewText: My 3 month old son has a blocked tear duct that has not cleared up as of yet. I keep these wipes in my purse and diaper bag, they are great for on the go when his eye needs a quick wipe. They are gentle and do not irritate his eye further. We will be giving some to daycare so that they can use them throughout the day as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Works really well! But it's very wet so you almost need to dry your kiddos eye after using it. I wish it was a little less wet.
